---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site, mailLink } from '../data/site';

const a = site.address;
---

<Layout
  current="/terms"
  title="Terms of Service - Kensons Garage | Car Body Repair South London"
  description="The terms on which Kensons Garage in Brixton provides body repair, resprays, servicing and insurance work, and uses this website."
  noindex={true}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of Service"
    crumb="Terms of Service"
  />

  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p><strong>Last updated: June 2026</strong></p>

        <p>
          These Terms of Service set out the basis on which {site.name} provides its services and on which
          you may use this website. By enquiring with us, booking work or using this site, you agree to
          these terms. Please read them carefully.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} is a family-run car body repair business based at {a.unit}, {a.street}, {a.area},
          {a.city} {a.postcode}. You can contact us by email at <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a> or by
          telephone on {site.phoneMobile} or {site.phoneSecondary}.
        </p>

        <h2>Services we provide</h2>
        <p>
          We provide vehicle body and collision repair services, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Body repair, dent and scratch repair, and accident damage restoration;</li>
          <li>Full and partial resprays and refinishing;</li>
          <li>Insurance and claims work;</li>
          <li>Vehicle servicing and maintenance;</li>
          <li>Brakes, wheels and rims;</li>
          <li>Customisation and interiors.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Quotes and estimates</h2>
        <p>
          We provide <strong>free, no-obligation quotes</strong> so you know the cost and scope of repairs
          before any work begins. Wherever possible we ask to see the damage — in person or from clear
          photos — so the estimate is accurate. We provide a clear estimate before work begins and aim for
          the final bill to match the quote. If, once work is under way, we discover additional damage or
          work that materially affects the price, we will contact you and obtain your approval before
          proceeding.
        </p>

        <h2>Bookings and your vehicle</h2>
        <p>
          Walk-ins are welcome, especially for minor damage that may be repaired the same day. For larger
          repairs we will agree a convenient date so we have the right time and resources. While your
          vehicle is with us we will take reasonable care of it. Please remove any valuables and personal
          belongings before leaving your vehicle, as we cannot accept responsibility for items left inside.
          Repair timescales are estimates given in good faith and may vary with the extent of the work or
          the availability of parts.
        </p>

        <h2>Payment</h2>
        <p>
          We offer flexible payment options, including <strong>BACS transfers</strong>,
          <strong>secure online payment links</strong> for convenience, and a <strong>card terminal</strong>
          for in-person payments. Soon, we will also be offering <strong>Klarna</strong> for flexible
          payment options. Payment is due on completion of the work unless we have agreed otherwise with
          you in advance.
        </p>

        <h2>Workmanship guarantee</h2>
        <p>
          All our repairs come with a <strong>workmanship guarantee</strong>, giving you peace of mind that
          the work is done to the highest standards. Please note this guarantee
          <strong>does not cover new damage from accidents, wear and tear, or issues unrelated to the
          original repair</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>Insurance work</h2>
        <p>
          We work directly with insurance companies to help ensure a smooth claims process. Where your
          repair is being handled as an insurance claim, the terms of your policy and your insurer's
          authorisation will apply alongside these terms. You remain responsible for any excess, or for any
          amounts your insurer does not cover, unless agreed otherwise.
        </p>

        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>
          We will carry out our work with reasonable care and skill. Nothing in these terms limits or
          excludes our liability for death or personal injury caused by our negligence, for fraud, or for
          any other liability that cannot lawfully be limited or excluded. Subject to that, we are not
          liable for losses that are not a foreseeable result of our work, or for pre-existing faults, wear
          and tear, or damage unrelated to the work we have carried out. Your statutory rights as a consumer
          are not affected by these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>This website</h2>
        <p>
          The content, design, text, images and branding on this website — including the
          <span class="tagline-art text-gold">This is Art</span> mark — are owned by or licensed to
          {site.name} and are protected by intellectual property laws. You may view and use the site for
          your own personal, non-commercial use. You may not copy, reproduce or republish any part of it
          without our permission. We provide the site on an "as is" basis and may update or change its
          content at any time.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of <strong>England &amp; Wales</strong>, and any disputes
          will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England &amp; Wales.
        </p>

        <h2>How to contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>{site.name}</strong></li>
          <li>{a.unit}, {a.street}, {a.area}, {a.city} {a.postcode}</li>
          <li>Email: <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li>Telephone: {site.phoneMobile} or {site.phoneSecondary}</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
